<p itemprop="description">The head of change and release management provides strategic leadership for all change and release activities across the organisation. They establish enterprise-wide policies, drive digital transformation initiatives, and ensure operational excellence in service delivery.</p>

<section class="role-details">
    <h2>Typical responsibilities</h2>
    <ul>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Provide strategic leadership for change and release management across the organisation</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Establish enterprise-wide change management policies and governance frameworks</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Drive digital transformation and DevOps adoption initiatives</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Lead organisational change capability development and maturity improvement</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Represent change management in senior leadership and board-level discussions</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Ensure alignment with business strategy and regulatory requirements</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Drive innovation and continuous improvement in operational practices</li>
    </ul>
</section>

